.TH "MAP.GETORINSERT" "3JS" "December 13, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Map.getOrInsert \- Map.prototype.getOrInsert()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]getOrInsert()\f[B]\f[R] method of \f[CR]Map\f[R]
instances returns the value corresponding to the specified key in this
\f[CR]Map\f[R].
If the key is not present, it inserts a new entry with the key and a
given default value, and returns the inserted value.
.PP
If the computation of the default value is expensive, consider using
\f[CR]Map.prototype.getOrInsertComputed()\f[R] instead, which takes a
callback to compute the default value only if it\(cqs actually needed.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] map = \f[B]new\f[R] Map([[\(dqbar\(dq, \(dqfoo\(dq]]);
console.log(map.getOrInsert(\(dqbar\(dq, \(dqdefault\(dq));
\f[I]// Expected output: \(dqfoo\(dq\f[R]

console.log(map.getOrInsert(\(dqbaz\(dq, \(dqdefault\(dq));
\f[I]// Expected output: \(dqdefault\(dq\f[R]
.EE
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
getOrInsert(key, defaultValue)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]key\f[R]
The key of the value to return from the \f[CR]Map\f[R] object.
Object keys are compared by reference, not by value.
.TP
\f[B]defaultValue\f[R]
The value to insert and return if the key is not already present in the
\f[CR]Map\f[R] object.
.SS Return value
The value associated with the specified key in the \f[CR]Map\f[R]
object.
If the key can\(cqt be found, \f[CR]defaultValue\f[R] is inserted and
returned.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \f[CR]getOrInsert()\f[R] method is equivalent to the following:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]if\f[R] (map.has(key)) {
  \f[B]return\f[R] map.get(key);
}
map.set(key, defaultValue);
\f[B]return\f[R] defaultValue;
.EE
.PP
It is also similar to the following pattern (which is slightly less
reliable if \f[CR]null\f[R] or \f[CR]undefined\f[R] are valid values in
your map):
.IP
.EX
map.set(key, map.get(key) ?? defaultValue);
.EE
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Multimap
In a map where each key is mapped to an array of values, you can use
\f[CR]getOrInsert()\f[R] to ensure that the array exists for a given key
before attempting to push a new value to the array.
.IP
.EX
map.getOrInsert(key, []).push(value);
.EE
.SS Applying default values
You can use \f[CR]getOrInsert()\f[R] to ensure that a key exists in a
map, even if you currently don\(cqt need its value.
This is usually to normalize user input.
.PP
Imagine you have a map of user preferences, and you want to ensure that
a certain preference is always set to a default value if the user
hasn\(cqt specified it:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] options = readConfig();
options.getOrInsert(\(dqtheme\(dq, \(dqlight\(dq);
options.getOrInsert(\(dqfontSize\(dq, 14);

\f[I]// Later in your code, you can safely assume these options exist\f[R]
document.body.dataset.theme = options.get(\(dqtheme\(dq);
.EE
